Comment: Original Triton compiler, forked into FlagTree as a unified
 multi-backend compiler for AI accelerators.

# --- Bundled / vendored components shipped inside the .deb ----------
#
# The wheel built from this source tree statically embeds several
# upstream artifacts that are downloaded at build time. They ship inside
# /usr/lib/python3/dist-packages/triton/ in the assembled .deb. Their
# licenses are listed below for attribution.

Files: usr/lib/python3/dist-packages/triton/_C/libtriton.so
       usr/lib/python3/dist-packages/triton/_C/libproton.so
Copyright: 2003-2024 LLVM contributors
License: Apache-2.0-with-LLVM-exception
Comment: Statically linked LLVM (commit 10dc3a8e, ~LLVM 18 era), pulled
 at build time from the OpenAI Triton llvm-builds CDN. See
 https://oaitriton.blob.core.windows.net/public/llvm-builds/ for the
 binary distribution and https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project for the
 source corresponding to the embedded commit.

Files: usr/lib/python3/dist-packages/triton/backends/nvidia/bin/ptxas
       usr/lib/python3/dist-packages/triton/backends/nvidia/bin/cuobjdump
Copyright: NVIDIA Corporation
License: NVIDIA-CUDA-EULA
Comment: NVIDIA CUDA Toolkit components (PTX assembler and cubin object
 dump) downloaded at build time from anaconda.org/nvidia. Distribution
 is governed by the NVIDIA CUDA Toolkit End User License Agreement at
 https://docs.nvidia.com/cuda/eula/. These files are NOT under a
 DFSG-free license; downstream packagers targeting Debian/Ubuntu main
 should split or unbundle them before re-distribution there.

Files: usr/lib/python3/dist-packages/pybind11/*
Copyright: 2016 Wenzel Jakob <wenzel.jakob@epfl.ch>, All rights reserved.
License: BSD-3-clause
Comment: pybind11 2.11.1, header-only library used to expose the C++
 dialect to Python. Embedded at build time from the upstream Triton
 build-deps tarball.

